cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with hand pose estimation from depth images. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as hand pose estimation is important for human-robot interaction. The use of multi-view projections and fusion of heat-maps suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories may also be relevant. Finally, the use of learned pose priors suggests that the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category may also be relevant.
